            <title>[KAFKA-983] Expose cleanshutdown method in MirrorMaker at the object level</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-983</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Making clean shutdown in MirrorMaker public at the object level will be useful. Currently if MirrorMaker is run in a container process, the only way to stop it seems to be triggering the shutdown hook (System.exit(0)) which may have unwarranted side effects on the other threads running in that container process. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
